situation: A 6m long prestressed cantilever beam carries a concentrated live load of 18kN at the free end and a uniform dead load due to its own weight. The unit weight of concrete is 20kN/m<sup>3</sup>. The strands are 12mm in diameter with total prestressing force of 540kN applied at an eccentricity "e" above the neutral axis of the gross-section. The beam has a width of 400mm and a total height of 600mm.

subquestions.question: What is the maximum stress (in MPa) in the bottom fiber of the beam at the free end when the eccentricity e=0?
What is the stress in the top fiber (in MPa) of the beam at the fixed end when the eccentricity e=100mm?
What is the required eccentricity (in mm) such that the stress at the top fibers of the beam at the fixed end is zero?
